The paper deals with optimization in deep networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of max-pooling and sub-sampling layers suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The MNIST dataset is a commonly used dataset for image classification, which further supports the focus on computer vision. The paper also discusses the reparameterization of network weights, which is a common technique in neural networks and falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE). The proposed weight updates are based on gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence, and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the results of training on an image segmentation problem, which is a common task in computer vision and falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
